-- Air France-KLM, Galapagos, Royal Vopak: European Equity Preview
-- B y   W h i t n e y   K i s l i n g
-- 2010-12-08T05:00:01Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-12-07/air-france-klm-galapagos-royal-vopak-european-equity-preview.html
The following companies’ shares may
have unusual moves in  European  trading. Stock symbols are in
parentheses, and prices are from the previous close.  The  Stoxx Europe 600 Index  rose 0.9 percent to 273.91. The
 Stoxx 50 Index  also gained 0.9 percent to 2,576.97. The  Euro
Stoxx 50 Index , a benchmark for nations using the euro, advanced
1.2 percent to 2,802.74.  Air France-KLM Group  (AF FP): France’s civil aviation
authority asked airlines to reduce flights in and out of Paris’s
Roissy-Charles de Gaulle airport, citing expected heavy
snowfall. Air France shares fell 2.2 percent to 14.01 euros.  Cybergun  (CYB FP): The maker of plastic guns said net
income rose 49 percent in the fiscal first half to 1.8 million
euros. The shares rose 0.6 percent to 12.10 euros.  Galapagos NV  (GLPG BB): The Belgian drug developer working
with five of the world’s 10 largest drugmakers by revenue raised
663,257 euros ($881,336) from the exercise of 76,157 warrants
granted to employees. Galapagos dropped 0.2 percent to 11.98
euros.  Royal Vopak NV  (VPK NA): The world’s largest chemical and
oil storage company said it obtained a 30-year fixed-rate loan
of 20 billion yen ($240 million) from a single, undisclosed
Asian investor. Vopak increased 0.3 percent to 36.42 euros.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Whitney Kisling in New York at 
 wkisling@bloomberg.net .  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Nick Baker at   nbaker7@bloomberg.net . 